except for one obvious browser which doesn't

00:02:52.900 --> 00:02:57.370
support, which I know you're doing work on
trying to rectify that with the plug-in you're

00:02:57.370 --> 00:03:02.780
developing. So I think as we get things like
supported, IE supported, that will start taking

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:06.980
off and it will become a real platform we
can develop too, like what Flash has been

00:03:06.980 --> 00:03:09.120
